#Text=Ontario Votes 2007 : Interview with Green Party candidate John Ogilvie , Carleton — Mississippi Mills
#Text=Sunday , October 7 , 2007
#Text=is running for the Green Party of Ontario in the Ontario provincial election , in the Carleton — Mississippi Mills riding .
#Text=Wikinews ' Nick Moreau interviewed him regarding his values , his experience , and his campaign .
#Text=Stay tuned for further interviews ; every candidate from every party is eligible , and will be contacted .

#Text=Expect interviews from Liberals , Progressive Conservatives , New Democratic Party members , Ontario Greens , as well as members from the Family Coalition , Freedom , Communist , Libertarian , and Confederation of Regions parties , as well as independents .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Why have you chosen to involve yourself in the political process ?
#Text=Why did you choose to run in this constituency ?
#Text=" History is made by those who show up " ( Benjamin Disraeli )
#Text=What prior political experience do you have ?
#Text=What skills and insight can you bring to office , from other non-political positions you may have held ?
#Text=I have no political experience , but I have built several tech businesses in the past decade and attracted CAD5 million in venture capital to these firms .
#Text=Which of your competitors do you expect to pose the biggest challenge to your candidacy ?
#Text=Why ?
#Text=What makes you the most desirable of all candidates running in the riding ?
#Text=What do you feel are the three most important issues to voters in your riding ?
#Text=Are these the same top three issues that are most important to you ?
#Text=What would you do to address these issues ?
#Text=The incumbent , Norm Sterling , is a political survivor .
#Text=He has been elected eight time for a total of thirty years .
#Text=Nobody really knows why .
#Text=I am the only businessman and entrepreneur among the candidates , and I have a vision and a plan .
#Text=My opponents have their party briefing books .
#Text=What should be the first order of business in the 39th Legislative Assembly ?
#Text=Catching up to California on emissions-standards and other pollution/climate measures .
#Text=I refuse to have Arnold come up here again and lecture us on how California is leading N. America on environmental issues .
#Text=Are the property taxes in your riding at a fair level for the amount of services received in the municipality ?
#Text=Local property taxes are rising way too fast for value delivered .
#Text=How can the province lead the way in stimulating job creation ?
#Text=By helping our local tech community lead the next global tech boom : green-tech .
#Text=What are your views on the mixed member proportional representation ( MMP ) referendum ?
#Text=We support it 100 % .
#Text=Without it , in the past , our province has lurched hard to the left or to the right with each election , like a car with only two gears , reverse and forward .
#Text=MMP would smooth out these destructive swings .
#Text=What role , if any , does " new media " play in your campaign , and the campaign of your party ?
#Text=( websites , blogs , Facebook , YouTube videos , etc )
#Text=Do you view it as beneficial , or a challenge ?
#Text=I have helped two dozen Green candidates put up a web presence ( http://vote-green.ca ) .
#Text=I blog every couple of days , and people seem to enjoy it .
#Text=Facebook is a waste of time .
#Text=Youtube is good , but it is very time-consuming to produce really good content .
#Text=Of the decisions made by Ontario 's 38th Legislative Assembly , which was the most beneficial to your this electoral district ?
#Text=To the province as a whole ?
#Text=Which was least beneficial , or even harmful , to your this riding ?
#Text=To the province as a whole ?
#Text=The cancellation of the Labour-Sponsored Investment Fund tax credit , without consultation , put the boot to a recovering tech startup industry .
#Text=This was very harmful .
#Text=I have been campaigning too long - I ca n't think of anything good to say about the Liberal govt : - )
